Able to export results of commands into a file such that 
no error message should be exported to the file and 
if the command has no output, no file should be created.

Able to see all the subdirectories with -R supplemented to Ls.

Through Ls, able to see the content of a path p, if p is a file, see its content.
and a reminder if p does not exist

Able to move a file or directory to another directory

Able to see the contents of both files if I add the contents of file A to file B,
but if file A for some reason is invalid, I should still be able to see file B

Able to retrieve a file by a URL

Able to keep working from my last session
Able to save my current session for next time

Able to search for all files with a certain name in a provided directory
Able to search for all directories with a certain name in a provided directory
Able to search for all files with a certain name in the provided 2 directories
Able to search for all directories with a certain name in the provided 2 directories
If one of the two directories I am searching in is invalid, let me know and keep searching the other directories.
Display the results in an acceptable manner

Able to see the entire file system in the manner of the a tree
